======================================
             SSM LIBRARY
   INSTALATION, COMPILATION RUNNING
=====================================

-> SSM project
see http://chaton.ethz.ch/wiki/index.php/SSM

compile2.sh	compile script for brutus
link2.sh	link script for brutus


SETUP: (tested by Gerardo Tauriello)
  module load gsl gcc blast ( for Root Finder)
  module load gcc open_mpi blitz/0.9.3 boost java/1.6 python


module load gcc open_mpi blitz/0.9.3 boost java/1.6 python gsl gcc blast

(versions used: open_mpi/1.4.5, boost/1.49.0, python/2.7.2, gcc/4.4.6, blitz/0.9.3, java/1.6.0_31)
- get and compile libsbml
-> from http://sourceforge.net/projects/sbml/files/libsbml/
-> execute: (change $HOME/more_libs if needed)
./configure --with-expat --with-python --with-java --prefix="$HOME/more_libs"

make -j 5
make install

- libexpat, blitz and boost available from brutus
- adapt compile2.sh and link2.sh (to change "$HOME/more_lib" if needed)
- Compile SSM with "./compile2.sh && ./link2.sh"
- USAGE: ./StochasticSimulationMethods <SBMLFILE>
-> generate sbml files (.xml) with MATLAB codes

NOTE: For instiallation is sometimes better do serial compilation, i.e. do
make -j instead of make - j 5
